comment_data.body:
Thanks for the report.  This looks like an IntelliJ platform issue...

@alexander-doroshko: any thoughts?

I can't say if it had any impacts as I was just updating and when it completed I just closed IntelliJ for the day.

My bet is that there was an error with the Flutter Plugin after the update and the plugin generated a scratch document with the issue text (which I posted before this one). Then this error triggered because of the scratch created by the Flutter plugin.

I have some other scratches, but since the Flutter plugin had just created one, it looks a bit of a coincidence.

I will get the logs when I get to my pc.

Oh, thanks, now I clearly see that this is a Flutter plugin issue :)
@pq @devoncarew  see https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/blame/master/src/io/flutter/FlutterErrorReportSubmitter.java#L190
